   - Headless Node.js simulation using ES modules (no DOM, no localStorage)
   - Three strategies: `random` (match-producing swaps only), `hint` (existing findBestSwap heuristic), `mcts` (MCTS with silent flag)
   - Goal types: `created` (cumulative tile creation), `blocked` (clear all blocked tiles), `current` (live board count), `score` (treated as always-met)
   - ASCII progress bar with `\r` reprinting: `█░` characters + rolling win rate
   - `silent` option added to `findBestSwapMCTS` to suppress per-move logging
   - MCTS cost: ~400ms/move at iters=500 depth=4, ~57ms/move at iters=100 depth=1
   - Main bottleneck: each `simulateMove` deep-clones board + runs full cascade

